article.headline: Siena 74, St. Peter's 63
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- Kenny Hasbrouck scored 33 points to lead Siena to a 74-63 win over St. Peter's Monday night. Alex Franklin added 15 points for the Saints (18-5, 12-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Siena jumped to a 7-0 lead, but St. Peter's (6-16, 3-9 MAAC) went on a 14-2 run to take a 14-9 lead midway through the first half. Nick Leon had two 3-pointers during the run. He wound up with 16 points for the Peacocks. Hasbrouck then took over. He scored all but two points in a 13-0 run that put the Saints up for good 31-22. They led 43-32 at intermission, and St. Peter's never cut the margin to less than nine points in the second half. Hasbrouck shot 11 for 19 from the field, including 4 of 7 from 3-point range, and was 7 of 8 from the free throw line. Ryan Rossiter had a game-high 10 rebounds for the Saints. Wesley Jenkins led the Peacocks with 18 points.
